{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2024-01-05","name":"Hugh de Mortimer","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Hugh de Mortimer","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Hugh"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Mortimer"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Hugh de Mortimer , of Wigmore","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1087–1148","fullLifespan":"1087–26 February 1148","portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/0a01m/thumb200s.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7780-114384-6314-2/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/141665918","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7780-114384-6314-2/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7780-114384-6314-2/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-99948-17-22/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/109080657","headline":"BIO","description":"BIO:  from http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/ENGLISH%20NOBILITY%20MEDIEVAL2.htm#RogerMortimerdied1214A as of 6/6/2016\n\nHUGH [II] de Mortimer, son of RALPH [I] de Mortimer & his [second/third wife Mabel …","@type":"MediaObject"}],"popularStory":{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-99948-17-22/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/109080657","headline":"BIO","description":"BIO:  from http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/ENGLISH%20NOBILITY%20MEDIEVAL2.htm#RogerMortimerdied1214A as of 6/6/2016\n\nHUGH [II] de Mortimer, son of RALPH [I] de Mortimer & his [second/third wife Mabel …","@type":"MediaObject"},"birthDate":"+1087","birthPlace":{"address":"Wigmore Castle, Herefordshire, England","geo":{"latitude":52.31813,"longitude":-2.869,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1148-02-26","deathPlace":{"address":"Wigmore, Herefordshire, England","geo":{"latitude":52.3161,"longitude":-2.861,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"Hugh de Mortimer (c.1100-26 February 1180/81) was a Norman English medieval lord.\n\nLineage\nThe son of Ranulph de Mortimer, he was Lord of Wigmore Castle, Stratfield Mortimer, Cleobury Mortimer and at times, Bridgnorth, Bishop's Castle and Maelienydd.\n\nAnarchy\nDuring the Anarchy of King Stephen's reign, Mortimer was an ardent royalist until at least 1148. This was because Wigmore Castle had been confiscated from his father by King Henry I. He only seems to have returned to England from his Norman estates in 1137.\n\nPrivate Wars\nHe did quarrel violently with his neighbouring Lords, most notably with Miles, earl of Hereford, his son Roger and Josce de Dinan, lord of Ludlow. The latter ambushed Mortimer and only released him after the payment of a substantial ransom. During this time Mortimer also took over the Royal castle at Bridgnorth.\n\nOpposition to King Henry II\nHugh was one of the Barons who objected to Henry II's demand for the return of Royal castles in 1155. Henry II launched a campaign in May 1155 against Hugh, simultaneously besieging his three principal castles of Wigmore, Bridgnorth and Cleobury. On 7 July 1155, Hugh formally submitted to Henry II at the Council at Bridgnorth. He was allowed to keep his own two castles (though Cleobury had been destroyed during the siege) but Bridgnorth returned to the crown.\n\nMarriage & issue\nBetween 1148 and 1155 Hugh married Maud le Meschin (also known as Maud/Matilde du Bessin), daughter of William Meschin, Lord of Skipton, Yorkshire, and Cecily de Rumilly. Maud (Matilda) was the widow of Philip Belmeis of Tong. Hugh and Maud's son Roger Mortimer of Wigmore succeeded his father as Lord of Wigmore. Hugh and Maud had three other sons, Hugh (killed in a tournament), Ralph, and William. Hugh may have died 26 Feb 1180/81 in Cleobury Mortimer, Shropshire, England, and was buried at Wigmore.","sourceList":[{"title":"Wikipedia - Ranulph de Mortimer","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranulph_de_Mortimer","sourceUri":"QF1V-51K"},{"title":"Hugh de Mortimer, of Wigmore","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"http://www.ancientwalesstudies.org/id104.html","sourceUri":"3FYD-L2J"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1087","date":"1087","place":"Wigmore Castle, Herefordshire, England"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1104","date":"1104","age":"17","id":"93QW-7B5"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1112","date":"about 1112","place":"Wigmore, Herefordshire, England","age":"25","id":"KH1H-67Y"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1117","date":"1117","place":"Wigmore, Herefordshire, England","age":"30","id":"LHKV-BD1"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1148","date":"26 February 1148","place":"Wigmore, Herefordshire, England","age":"61"}],"parent":[{"name":"Lord Ranulph de Mortimer","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1050–1104","birthDate":"A+1050","deathDate":"+1104","age":54,"portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/i5jkm/thumb64.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"@type":"Person","identifier":"93QW-7B5","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/93QW-7B5/lord-ranulph-de-mortimer-1050-1104","published":true},{"name":"Lady Mabel Mortimer","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1060–Female","birthDate":"+1060","@type":"Person","identifier":"GJ8T-X27","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/GJ8T-X27/mabel-1060","published":true}],"sibling":[{"name":"Hugh de Mortimer","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1087–1148","birthDate":"+1087","deathDate":"+1148-02-26","age":61,"portrait":{"url":"http